<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
        <title>Doppar</title>
        <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
        <style>*{box-sizing:border-box}body{margin:0;padding:40px 20px;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;background:#f9fafb;color:#111827;text-align:center}header img{width:48px;height:auto;margin-bottom:10px}h1{font-size:2rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:10px}.version{font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;margin-bottom:30px}.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:20px;max-width:1000px;margin:0 auto 40px}.card{background:#fff;padding:20px;border:1px solid #d1d5db;border-radius:12px;text-align:left;transition:box-shadow .2s}.card:hover{box-shadow:0 4px 12px rgba(0,0,0,.05)}.card h3{font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:8px}.card p{font-size:14px;color:#4b5563}code{background:#e5e7eb;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-family:monospace}</style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <header>
            <img src="[[ enqueue('logo.png') ]]" alt="Logo" />
            <h1>Default Controller Page</h1>
            <p class="version">You are viewing the framework's default page for <strong>[[ $className ]]</strong>.</p>
        </header>

        <section class="grid">
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Generated Files</h3>
                <p>The following files were created for you:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Controller: <code>[[ controllerPath ]]</code></li>
                    <li>View: <code>resources/views/[[ routeName ]]/default.odo.php</code></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <a href="https://doppar.com/versions/3.x/controllers.html" class="card">
                <h3>Read the Controllers Guide</h3>
                <p>Learn how to add actions, return views/responses, and organize routes.</p>
            </a>
        </section>
    </body>
</html>
